Here are the important files and folders in a Paper Mario DX mod.

{% filetree %}
- README.md
- assets
  - **mod** Where you will place your mod's assets
    - …
  - dx Assets provided by DX (**do not edit**)
    - … 
  - us Assets dumped from the baserom (**do not edit**)
    - …
- include C headers
  - …
- src C code
  - dx
    - **config.h** Mod configuration
  - …
- … Other files/folders are internal to DX
{% /filetree %}

## The `assets` folder

The `assets` folder contains game content (not engine code).

It has a layered approach where `assets/mod/` takes priority over `assets/dx/`, which takes priority over `assets/us/`.
For example, the file `assets/us/msg/0C_Chapter1.msg` can be overridden by creating a file at `assets/mod/msg/0C_Chapter1.msg`.
You can create the `msg` folder if it doesn't exist.

{% aside type="caution" %}
You should **only** create, modify, or delete files in `assets/mod/`. **Never** edit `assets/dx/` or `assets/us`.
{% /aside %}

## The `src` and `include` folders

These folders contain C code for the game engine. You can edit it freely, just note that you may get merge conflicts
when updating to a new version of DX.

## The `src/dx/config.h` file

This is where you configure mod settings like the [mod name and new game start](/develop/title-screen), the [debug menu](/develop/testing/debug-menu), and more. You don't need to understand C code to use these options — just edit the file.
